---
// The trigram index as a pruning funnel, using the post's measured numbers for
// `MakeCallback`: ten trigrams ANDed together cut 47,890 files to 119 candidates
// in under half a millisecond, and only then does the real regex run, confirming
// 87 matches. Hand-authored SVG so it renders server-side and themes via the
// shared figure.diagram CSS variables.
---

<figure class="diagram trigram-diagram">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 760 200" role="img"
    aria-label="MakeCallback compiles to ten trigrams. Intersecting their posting lists narrows 47,890 files to 119 candidates in under half a millisecond, and the regex then confirms 87 matches.">
    <defs>
      <marker id="tg-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="8.5" refY="5"
        markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" />
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <text class="tg-query" x="380" y="30" text-anchor="middle">MakeCallback → Mak ∧ ake ∧ keC ∧ eCa ∧ Cal ∧ all ∧ llb ∧ lba ∧ bac ∧ ack</text>

    <!-- edges -->
    <line class="edge" x1="207" y1="116" x2="281" y2="116" marker-end="url(#tg-arrow)" />
    <line class="edge" x1="477" y1="116" x2="551" y2="116" marker-end="url(#tg-arrow)" />
    <text class="edge-label" x="244" y="100" text-anchor="middle">intersect</text>
    <text class="edge-label" x="244" y="146" text-anchor="middle">0.45 ms</text>
    <text class="edge-label" x="514" y="100" text-anchor="middle">run regex</text>

    <!-- boxes -->
    <g class="node">
      <rect class="box" x="15" y="88" width="192" height="58" rx="8" />
      <text class="box-label" x="111" y="112">47,890 files</text>
      <text class="box-sub" x="111" y="131">the whole tree</text>
    </g>
    <g class="node">
      <rect class="box" x="283" y="88" width="192" height="58" rx="8" />
      <text class="box-label" x="379" y="112">119 candidates</text>
      <text class="box-sub" x="379" y="131">0.25% survive</text>
    </g>
    <g class="node">
      <rect class="box" x="553" y="88" width="192" height="58" rx="8" />
      <text class="box-label" x="649" y="112">87 matches</text>
      <text class="box-sub" x="649" y="131">confirmed by regex</text>
    </g>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    The trigram AND does the cheap work, throwing out 99.75% of the tree before the real regex runs, so the
    expensive matcher only ever opens 119 files.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  figure.trigram-diagram .tg-query {
    fill: var(--muted); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace; font-size: 12.5px;
  }
  figure.trigram-diagram .box-sub {
    fill: var(--muted); font-size: 12px; text-anchor: middle;
  }
</style>
